rath.libxml

Class SAXAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • rath.libxml.SAXAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SAXHandler

    public class SAXAdapter
extends Object
implements SAXHandler
    Default base class for SAX2 event handlers.

    This class is available as a convenience base class for SAX2 applications.

    Application writers can extend this class when they need to implement only part of an interface; parser writers can instantiate this class to provide default handlers when the application has not supplied its own.

    Author:
    Jang-Ho Hwang, rath@xrath.com

      • fatalError

        public void fatalError(LibXmlException exception)
        Description copied from interface: SAXHandler
        Report a fatal XML parsing error. The default implementation does nothing. Application writers may override this method in a subclass if they need to take specific actions for each fatal error (such as collecting all of the errors into a single report): in any case, the application must stop all regular processing when this method is invoked, since the document is no longer reliable, and the parser may no longer report parsing events.
        Specified by:
        fatalError in interface SAXHandler
        Parameters:
        exception - The error information with an exception.
